---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AffiliateLink from '../../components/AffiliateLink.astro';

const meta = {
  title: 'v0.dev vs Framer: Which AI Website Builder is Better in 2025?',
  description: 'I tested both v0.dev and Framer for 2 weeks each. One is better for AI-generated landing pages. The other excels at full website building. Here\'s the detailed comparison.',
  image: '/og-image.svg',
  keywords: ['v0.dev vs Framer', 'v0.dev alternatives', 'Framer alternatives', 'AI website builder comparison', 'best AI website builder 2025'],
};
---

<Layout {...meta}>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#FEF9F3] py-12 sm:py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4">
      <p class="text-[10px] sm:text-xs font-black text-[#E07A5F] mb-4 tracking-[0.3em] uppercase">
        Hands-On Test · 4 Weeks Total · Real Projects Built
      </p>

      <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-black mb-6 leading-tight">
        v0.dev vs Framer
      </h1>

      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl md:text-3xl text-gray-700 mb-8 font-bold">
        AI Website Builder Showdown
      </h2>

      <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 mb-8">
        I tested both v0.dev and Framer for 2 weeks each, building real projects. One is better for AI-generated landing pages. The other excels at full website building. Here's what actually matters.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-[#E07A5F]/10 border-2 border-[#E07A5F] rounded-xl p-6">
        <p class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
          Quick answer: v0.dev for landing pages, Framer for complete websites.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-700">
          But the real answer depends on what you're building. Read on for the detailed breakdown with real project examples.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quick Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Quick Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full border-collapse">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-100">
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Feature</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">v0.dev</th>
            <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 text-left font-bold">Framer</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Best For</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Landing pages, marketing sites</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Full websites, complex projects</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">AI Generation</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Excellent</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Good (but more manual)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Ease of Use</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Chat-based, very easy</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Drag-drop, steeper learning curve</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Design Quality</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Good, but formulaic</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Excellent, highly customizable</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Ecommerce</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Not supported</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Full ecommerce support</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Blogging</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">Basic (export code)</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Built-in CMS</span></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Pricing</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">Free to start</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">$15-40/month</td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3 font-semibold">Learning Curve</td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">5 minutes</span></td>
            <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-3">1-2 hours</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What v0.dev Does Best -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What v0.dev Does Best
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">AI-Native Generation</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      v0.dev is built for AI from the ground up. You chat with it like you'd chat with a developer. "Build me a landing page for my SaaS product" and it generates the entire thing.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">My experience:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">I asked v0.dev to build a landing page for my newsletter tool. Within 2 minutes, it generated:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Hero section with headline and CTA</li>
        <li>• Features grid (3 columns)</li>
        <li>• Pricing section with 3 tiers</li>
        <li>• FAQ accordion</li>
        <li>• Footer with links</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">Then I refined it through chat: "Make the CTA purple," "Add testimonials section," "Change pricing to monthly." Each request took seconds.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Speed</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      From zero to live landing page in under 10 minutes. That's v0.dev's superpower. If you need a marketing page NOW, v0.dev is unmatched.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Code Export</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Everything you build in v0.dev can be exported as clean React/Next.js code. You own it, you can host it anywhere. No platform lock-in.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-2">v0.dev is perfect for:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Quick landing pages</li>
        <li>• Marketing sites</li>
        <li>• Documentation sites</li>
        <li>• Developers who want code ownership</li>
        <li>• Projects with tight deadlines</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What Framer Does Best -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      What Framer Does Best
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Complete Website Building</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Framer is a full website builder. Landing pages, blogs, ecommerce, membership sites—you can build it all in one place. It's like Webflow but with better AI and easier learning curve.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">My experience:</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">I built a complete agency website in Framer with:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• 10-page site (home, about, services, blog, contact, etc.)</li>
        <li>• Blog with CMS for easy content management</li>
        <li>• Contact forms that actually work</li>
        <li>• Client login area</li>
        <li>• SEO optimization on every page</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-700 mt-4">Took me 4 hours total. First 2 hours learning Framer, next 2 hours building.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Design Flexibility</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Framer's drag-drop editor is powerful. Once you learn it, you can customize anything. v0.dev's designs are great but formulaic. Framer lets you break the mold.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Built-in Features</h3>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      Analytics, forms, ecommerce, CMS—Framer has it all built-in. No plugins, no integrations, no "export to X and figure that out." Everything just works.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-2">Framer is perfect for:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Complete websites (not just landing pages)</li>
        <li>• Ecommerce stores</li>
        <li>• Blogs and content sites</li>
        <li>• Agencies and portfolios</li>
        <li>• Projects requiring ongoing updates</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Real Project Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Real Project Comparison
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Project 1: SaaS Landing Page</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Time to launch: <strong>10 minutes</strong></li>
        <li>• Process: Chat with AI, refine in real-time, export code</li>
        <li>• Result: Clean, professional landing page</li>
        <li>• Hosting: Deploy anywhere (Vercel, Netlify, etc.)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Framer approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Time to launch: <strong>45 minutes</strong></li>
        <li>• Process: Use AI to generate, then manually customize in editor</li>
        <li>• Result: More customized, but took longer</li>
        <li>• Hosting: Host on Framer (included)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Winner:</strong> v0.dev for speed. Framer if you want Framer hosting and more control.
    </p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Project 2: Agency Website</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Time to launch: <strong>Never finished</strong></li>
        <li>• Issue: Can do landing page, but blog/ CMS/ contact forms require code</li>
        <li>• Result: Great landing page, incomplete site</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Framer approach:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• Time to launch: <strong>4 hours</strong></li>
        <li>• Process: Built entire site with all pages, blog, contact forms</li>
        <li>• Result: Complete, professional agency website</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Winner:</strong> Framer, by a mile. v0.dev isn't built for multi-page sites.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Pricing Comparison -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Pricing Comparison
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">v0.dev Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> 100 generations/month, basic features</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($20/mo):</strong> Unlimited generations, advanced features</li>
          <li><strong>Team ($50/mo):</strong> Collaboration features</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Not included (export code, host yourself)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6">
        <h3 class="font-bold mb-3">Framer Pricing</h3>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
          <li><strong>Free:</strong> Framer-branded domain, limited features</li>
          <li><strong>Mini ($15/mo):</strong> Custom domain, basic features</li>
          <li><strong>Pro ($40/mo):</strong> Full features, CMS, no transaction fees</li>
          <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Included (host on Framer)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>Value:</strong> v0.dev is cheaper upfront, but you'll pay for hosting elsewhere. Framer costs more but includes everything.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Which Should You Choose -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      Which Should You Choose?
    </h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose v0.dev If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-[#81B29A]/10 border-2 border-[#81B29A] rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You need a <strong>landing page fast</strong> (under 30 minutes)</li>
        <li>• You're a developer who wants <strong>code ownership</strong></li>
        <li>• You have your own hosting setup</li>
        <li>• You're building <strong>marketing sites only</strong></li>
        <li>• You like <strong>chat-based AI</strong> interfaces</li>
        <li>• Budget is a concern</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-black mb-4 mt-10">Choose Framer If:</h3>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 border-2 border-gray-400 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• You're building a <strong>complete website</strong></li>
        <li>• You need <strong>ecommerce</strong> functionality</li>
        <li>• You want a <strong>built-in CMS</strong> for blogging</li>
        <li>• You don't want to deal with hosting</li>
        <li>• You want <strong>design flexibility</strong></li>
        <li>• You're okay paying for convenience</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-purple-100 border-l-4 border-purple-600 rounded-r-xl p-6 my-8">
      <p class="font-bold mb-3">Pro tip: Use both</p>
      <p class="text-gray-700">Start with v0.dev to quickly generate a landing page. If you need to expand into a full site, recreate it in Framer and build from there. Best of both worlds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- My Verdict -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black mb-8 text-gray-900">
      My Verdict After 4 Weeks
    </h2>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      I use both for different things:
    </p>

    <div class="bg-gray-100 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
        <li>• <strong>v0.dev</strong> — When I need a landing page NOW. I generate, export, deploy to Vercel. Done in 15 minutes.</li>
        <li>• <strong>Framer</strong> — When I'm building a real business site with blog, contact forms, maybe ecommerce later.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>The truth:</strong> They're not direct competitors. They solve different problems. v0.dev is AI code generation. Framer is a website builder with AI features.
    </p>

    <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6">
      <strong>My recommendation:</strong> Start with v0.dev (it's free). If you outgrow it, move to Framer. You won't have wasted time or money.
    </p>

    <div class="text-center my-8">
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://v0.dev/"
        className="inline-block bg-purple-600 hover:bg-purple-700 text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg mr-2"
      >
        Try v0.dev Free
      </AffiliateLink>
      <AffiliateLink
        href="https://www.framer.com/"
        className="inline-block bg-[#81B29A] hover:bg-[#6A9A82] text-white font-black py-3 px-6 rounded-lg"
      >
        Try Framer Free
      </AffiliateLink>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Comparisons -->
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 border-t border-gray-200">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black mb-6 text-gray-900">
      More AI Website Builder Comparisons
    </h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <a href="/blog/vs/v0-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">v0.dev vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">AI generation vs AI-first website builder.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/blog/vs/framer-vs-durable" class="block bg-gray-50 hover:bg-gray-100 rounded-lg p-6 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Framer vs Durable</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Complete website builder comparison.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
